@page "/e2e/gantt-v3"
@using System.Text.Json
@using Lumeo.GanttV3
@using Lumeo.Tests.ServerHost.E2E
@using Lumeo.Services

@* Gantt v2/v3 parity harness (feat/gantt-v3, T4) — v3 counterpart of
   GanttV2Page.razor. Renders the working-name Gantt3 against the IDENTICAL
   fixture + params (Height/GroupBy/BarColor) so every DOM measurement taken
   here has a like-for-like v2 baseline. See GanttV2Page.razor's remarks for
   the ?fixture / ?viewMode query params.

   Phase 2, T4 (drag parity suite) additions:
   - ?readonly=1 -> Gantt3.Readonly (shared with v2's ?readonly=1).
   - ?allowCreate=1 -> Gantt3.AllowCreate (v3-only; REUI parity, no v2 equivalent).
   - ?candrop=1 -> wires a CanDrop predicate that rejects any proposed drag/resize
     landing with Start earlier than GanttParityFixtures.CanDropBlackoutBefore
     (see that field's remarks for why 2026-03-05 against fixture task "fe3" is a
     clean, deterministic boundary) and counts every real ValidateDrop
     invocation into a sink (data-testid="candrop-call-count") so the E2E specs
     can assert the "0 calls when unset / 1 per snapped position / 0 during
     progress or create" call-frequency contract against the ACTUAL JS->.NET
     interop, not just BuildDragOptions' hasCanDrop flag (which is all bUnit
     could already assert without a real browser).
   - Event sinks (click/dateChange/progressChange/taskUpdate/taskCreate) mirror
     GanttV2Page.razor's — same rationale, same hidden <pre> convention. Also
     TasksChanged is bound (making this route "controlled" in Gantt3's
     controlled/uncontrolled discriminator sense) purely as a pass-through
     (always accepts what Gantt3 pushes) so a created task's ids are observable
     in their own sink without ever vetoing/reverting an edit.

   ?rtl=1 (Codex round 3, P2 #7): wraps Gantt3 in Lumeo's own DirectionProvider
   (the standard idiom every RTL-aware Lumeo component relies on — see
   DirectionProvider.razor's own remarks — sets dir="rtl" on a wrapping div,
   which every logical-CSS utility and gantt-v3.js's own RTL scrollLeft
   normalization resolve against) instead of a page-specific ad-hoc dir
   attribute, so this harness exercises the SAME code path a real RTL
   consumer would use.

   ?tree=0 (Codex round 4, P2 #2): every fixture on this page always passes a
   non-null GroupBy, which unconditionally satisfies GanttRowModel.
   DefaultShowTreePane's "GroupBy is set" branch regardless of whether any
   task actually HAS a GroupLabel — meaning the tree pane always renders here
   by default. The P2 #2 regression spec needs a like-for-like "without tree"
   comparison case (does scroll-centering math still land correctly when
   there's no tree-width offset to add at all), so this explicitly overrides
   Gantt3's ShowTreePane parameter to false when present.

   OnTaskClick sink (Codex round 5 review, Minor): the round-5 click-
   composition fix (P1 #1) only had bUnit coverage, which can't prove real
   DOM event bubbling — this host wires OnTaskClick to a plain
   data-testid="gantt-v3-last-clicked" element (AND the Phase-2 click
   event-sink JSON below, from the same handler) so an E2E spec can drive a
   REAL Playwright click on a rendered bar and assert the handler actually
   fired, closing that gap.

   data-testid="gantt-v3-toggle-direction" (Codex round 7 review, P2 #4):
   always wraps Gantt3 in ONE DirectionProvider whose Direction is a mutable
   field (seeded from ?rtl=1, same as before) instead of only conditionally
   wrapping it — lets a spec flip direction on an ALREADY-MOUNTED chart via a
   real Blazor re-render (the same path a live DirectionProvider ancestor
   toggling Direction would take in a real app), rather than only ever
   observing direction fixed at page load. *@

<PageTitle>E2E - Gantt v3</PageTitle>

<div class="p-4" style="max-width: 1600px;">
    <h1 data-testid="gantt-e2e-title">Gantt v3 (parity fixture)</h1>
    <div data-testid="gantt-v3-last-clicked">@_lastClickedTaskId</div>
    <DirectionProvider Direction="@_direction">
        <Gantt3 Tasks="@_tasks"
                TasksChanged="HandleTasksChanged"
                ViewMode="@_viewMode"
                ViewModeChanged="@(m => _viewMode = m)"
                Height="900px"
                GroupBy="@(t => t.GroupLabel ?? "")"
                ShowTreePane="@_showTreePaneOverride"
                BarColor="@GanttParityFixtures.GetBarColor"
                Readonly="@_readonly"
                AllowCreate="@_allowCreate"
                CanDrop="@(_useCanDrop ? CanDropHandler : null)"
                OnTaskClick="HandleTaskClick"
                OnDateChange="HandleDateChange"
                OnProgressChange="HandleProgressChange"
                OnTaskUpdate="HandleTaskUpdate"
                OnTaskCreate="HandleTaskCreate"
                data-testid="gantt-v3-root" />
    </DirectionProvider>

    <pre data-testid="event-sink-click" style="display:none">@_lastClickJson</pre>
    <pre data-testid="event-sink-datechange" style="display:none">@_lastDateChangeJson</pre>
    <pre data-testid="event-sink-progresschange" style="display:none">@_lastProgressChangeJson</pre>
    <pre data-testid="event-sink-taskupdate" style="display:none">@_lastTaskUpdateJson</pre>
    <pre data-testid="event-sink-taskcreate" style="display:none">@_lastTaskCreateJson</pre>
    <pre data-testid="event-sink-taskschanged" style="display:none">@_lastTasksChangedJson</pre>
    <pre data-testid="candrop-call-count" style="display:none">@_validateDropCallCount</pre>
    @* Bug fix (cx7b review): kept BELOW the chart, not above it - the visual
       snapshot suite screenshots a FIXED viewport clip from (0,0), so any
       harness control placed ABOVE the chart shifts the whole captured
       region down and stale-breaks every v3 baseline (exactly what adding
       this button above the chart did in round 7). A control added here in
       the future won't repeat that. *@
    <button type="button" data-testid="gantt-v3-toggle-direction" @onclick="ToggleDirection">Toggle direction</button>
</div>

@code {
    [SupplyParameterFromQuery] public string? Fixture { get; set; }
    [SupplyParameterFromQuery] public string? ViewMode { get; set; }
    [SupplyParameterFromQuery] public string? Readonly { get; set; }
    [SupplyParameterFromQuery] public string? AllowCreate { get; set; }
    [SupplyParameterFromQuery(Name = "candrop")] public string? CanDropQuery { get; set; }
    [SupplyParameterFromQuery] public string? Rtl { get; set; }
    [SupplyParameterFromQuery] public string? Tree { get; set; }

    private GanttViewMode _viewMode = GanttViewMode.Day;
    private List<GanttTask> _tasks = new();
    private bool _readonly;
    private bool _allowCreate;
    private bool _useCanDrop;
    private int _validateDropCallCount;
    private bool? _showTreePaneOverride;
    private string _lastClickedTaskId = "";
    private LayoutDirection _direction = LayoutDirection.Ltr;

    private string? _lastClickJson;
    private string? _lastDateChangeJson;
    private string? _lastProgressChangeJson;
    private string? _lastTaskUpdateJson;
    private string? _lastTaskCreateJson;
    private string? _lastTasksChangedJson;

    private void ToggleDirection() =>
        _direction = _direction == LayoutDirection.Ltr ? LayoutDirection.Rtl : LayoutDirection.Ltr;

    protected override void OnInitialized()
    {
        _tasks = Fixture switch
        {
            "today" => GanttParityFixtures.TodayMarkerTasks(),
            "tall" => GanttParityFixtures.TallFixture(),
            "future" => GanttParityFixtures.FutureOnlyFixture(),
            "crossing" => GanttParityFixtures.CrossingDependencyFixture(),
            _ => GanttParityFixtures.SharedTasks(),
        };
        if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(ViewMode) && Enum.TryParse<GanttViewMode>(ViewMode, out var parsed))
            _viewMode = parsed;
        _readonly = Readonly == "1";
        _allowCreate = AllowCreate == "1";
        _useCanDrop = CanDropQuery == "1";
        if (Tree == "0") _showTreePaneOverride = false;
        if (Rtl == "1") _direction = LayoutDirection.Rtl;
    }

    // Phase 2, T2/T3 (drag-parity sinks) + Codex round 5 review (real-DOM
    // click proof) share this one handler: sets the plain last-clicked-id
    // sink AND serializes the full task into the click event-sink JSON, so
    // a single Playwright click can drive both assertions.
    private Task HandleTaskClick(GanttTask t)
    {
        _lastClickedTaskId = t.Id;
        _lastClickJson = JsonSerializer.Serialize(t);
        return Task.CompletedTask;
    }

    private Task HandleDateChange(GanttTask t)
    {
        _lastDateChangeJson = JsonSerializer.Serialize(t);
        return Task.CompletedTask;
    }

    private Task HandleProgressChange(GanttTask t)
    {
        _lastProgressChangeJson = JsonSerializer.Serialize(t);
        return Task.CompletedTask;
    }

    private Task HandleTaskUpdate(GanttTaskUpdate u)
    {
        _lastTaskUpdateJson = JsonSerializer.Serialize(new { u.Task, Source = u.Source.ToString() });
        return Task.CompletedTask;
    }

    private Task HandleTaskCreate(GanttTaskUpdate u)
    {
        _lastTaskCreateJson = JsonSerializer.Serialize(new { u.Task, Source = u.Source.ToString() });
        return Task.CompletedTask;
    }

    private Task HandleTasksChanged(IEnumerable<GanttTask> tasks)
    {
        // Pass-through only: never vetoes, so this binding cannot alter behavior
        // for any route that doesn't exercise it (existing bar/arrow/nav specs
        // never fire a task edit, so _tasks here never actually changes for them).
        _tasks = tasks.ToList();
        _lastTasksChangedJson = JsonSerializer.Serialize(new { Count = _tasks.Count, Ids = _tasks.Select(t => t.Id) });
        return Task.CompletedTask;
    }

    private bool CanDropHandler(GanttTask task, GanttScheduleDropContext context)
    {
        // CanDrop is a plain Func, not an EventCallback — invoked synchronously
        // from GanttTimeline.ValidateDrop's [JSInvokable] method body, so unlike
        // the EventCallback-bound sinks above (whose receivers Blazor
        // auto-re-renders after invocation) mutating this page's own field here
        // does NOT by itself schedule a re-render of THIS component. Without an
        // explicit StateHasChanged, the candrop-call-count sink's <pre> would
        // never actually update in the DOM even though the field's value did —
        // invisible to a real browser/Playwright assertion.
        _validateDropCallCount++;
        var valid = context.ProposedStart >= GanttParityFixtures.CanDropBlackoutBefore;
        StateHasChanged();
        return valid;
    }
}
